theorem Topology.interiorClosure_idempotent
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆ interior (closure A)`
    have h₁ : (interior (closure (interior (closure A))) : Set X) ⊆
        closure (interior (closure A)) := interior_subset
    have h₂ : (closure (interior (closure A)) : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
      closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)
    have h₃ : (interior (closure (interior (closure A))) : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
      Set.Subset.trans h₁ h₂
    have h₄ : (interior (closure (interior (closure A))) : Set X) ⊆
        interior (closure A) := interior_mono h₃
    simpa using h₄
  · -- `interior (closure A) ⊆ interior (closure (interior (closure A)))`
    have h₁ : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
      subset_closure
    have h₂ : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆
        interior (closure (interior (closure A))) := by
      have := interior_mono h₁
      simpa [interior_interior] using this
    simpa using h₂

theorem Topology.interiorClosure_idempotent
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) = interior (closure A) := by
  -- First, prove the inclusion `⊆`.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    have h₁ : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
      have : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
      exact closure_mono this
    exact interior_mono h₁
  ·
    have h₂ : (interior (closure A) : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
      subset_closure
    have h_open : IsOpen (interior (closure A)) := isOpen_interior
    exact interior_maximal h₂ h_open

theorem Topology.closureInteriorClosure_eq_closure_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen A) :
    closure (interior (closure A)) = closure A := by
  -- Inclusion `⊆`.
  have h₁ : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)
  -- Inclusion `⊇`.
  have h₂ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    -- First, `A ⊆ interior (closure A)` because `A` is open.
    have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
      have : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
        interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
      simpa [hA.interior_eq] using this
    -- Taking closures yields the desired inclusion.
    exact closure_mono h_subset
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem Topology.closureInteriorClosure_subset_closure' {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
  have h : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
  simpa [closure_closure] using closure_mono h
